{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So, I kind of believe that we're in like the \"cave-painting\" era of computer interfaces."},{"time":5000,"text":"Like, they're very kind of -- they don't go as deep or as emotionally engaging as they possibly could be"},{"time":9000,"text":"and I'd like to change all that."},{"time":11000,"text":"Hit me."},{"time":14000,"text":"OK. So I mean, this is the kind of status quo interface, right?"},{"time":17000,"text":"It's very flat, kind of rigid."},{"time":19000,"text":"And OK, so you could sex it up and like go to a much more lickable Mac,"},{"time":23000,"text":"you know, but really it's the kind of same old crap we've had for the last,"},{"time":27000,"text":"you know, 30 years."},{"time":29000,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":32000,"text":"Like I think we really put up with a lot of crap with our computers."},{"time":35000,"text":"I mean it's point and click, it's like the menus, icons, it's all the kind of same thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40000,"text":"And so one kind of information space that I take inspiration from is my real desk."},{"time":44000,"text":"It's so much more subtle, so much more visceral"},{"time":48000,"text":"-- you know, what's visible, what's not."},{"time":50000,"text":"And I'd like to bring that experience to the desktop."},{"time":53000,"text":"So I kind of have a -- this is BumpTop."},{"time":57000,"text":"It's kind of like a new approach to desktop computing."},{"time":60000,"text":"So you can bump things -- they're all physically, you know, manipulable and stuff."},{"time":67000,"text":"And instead of that point and click, it's like a push and pull,"},{"time":70000,"text":"things collide as you'd expect them. Just like on my real desk,"},{"time":74000,"text":"I can -- let me just grab these guys -- I can turn things into piles"},{"time":77000,"text":"instead of just the folders that we have."},{"time":83000,"text":"And once things are in a pile I can browse them by throwing them into a grid,"},{"time":87000,"text":"or you know, flip through them like a book"},{"time":90000,"text":"or I can lay them out like a deck of cards."},{"time":95000,"text":"When they're laid out, I can pull things to new locations or delete things"},{"time":100000,"text":"or just quickly sort a whole pile, you know, just immediately, right?"},{"time":105000,"text":"And then, it's all smoothly animated, instead of these jarring changes you see in today's interfaces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110000,"text":"Also, if I want to add something to a pile, well, how do I do that?"},{"time":112000,"text":"I just toss it to the pile, and it's added right to the top. It's a kind of nice way."},{"time":118000,"text":"Also some of the stuff we can do is,"},{"time":120000,"text":"for these individual icons we thought -- I mean,"},{"time":122000,"text":"how can we play with the idea of an icon, and push that further?"},{"time":125000,"text":"And one of the things I can do is make it bigger"},{"time":128000,"text":"if I want to emphasize it and make it more important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130000,"text":"But what's really cool is that since there's a physics simulation running under this,"},{"time":134000,"text":"it's actually heavier. So the lighter stuff doesn't really move"},{"time":139000,"text":"but if I throw it at the lighter guys, right?"},{"time":143000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":146000,"text":"So it's cute, but it's also like a subtle channel of conveying information, right?"},{"time":151000,"text":"This is heavy so it feels more important. So it's kind of cool."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154000,"text":"Despite computers everywhere paper really hasn't disappeared,"},{"time":157000,"text":"because it has a lot of, I think, valuable properties."},{"time":159000,"text":"And some of those we wanted to transfer to the icons in our system."},{"time":162000,"text":"So one of the things you can do to our icons, just like paper, is crease them and fold them,"},{"time":166000,"text":"just like paper. Remember, you know, something for later."},{"time":170000,"text":"Or if you want to be destructive, you can just crumple it up"},{"time":173000,"text":"and, you know, toss it to the corner."},{"time":176000,"text":"Also just like paper, around our workspace"},{"time":179000,"text":"we'll pin things up to the wall to remember them later,"},{"time":181000,"text":"and I can do the same thing here,"},{"time":184000,"text":"and you know, you'll see post-it notes and things like that around people's offices."},{"time":187000,"text":"And I can pull them off when I want to work with them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189000,"text":"So, one of the criticisms of this kind of approach to organization is that,"},{"time":194000,"text":"you know, \"Okay, well my real desk is really messy. I don't want that mess on my computer.\""},{"time":198000,"text":"So one thing we have for that is like a grid align,"},{"time":201000,"text":"kind of -- so you get that more traditional desktop. Things are kind of grid aligned."},{"time":205000,"text":"More boring, but you still have that kind of colliding and bumping."},{"time":208000,"text":"And you can still do fun things like make shelves on your desktop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215000,"text":"Let's just break this shelf. Okay, that shelf broke."},{"time":218000,"text":"I think beyond the icons, I think another really cool domain for this software --"},{"time":223000,"text":"I think it applies to more than just icons and your desktop -- but browsing photographs."},{"time":229000,"text":"I think you can really enrich the way we browse our photographs"},{"time":232000,"text":"and bring it to that kind of shoebox of, you know, photos with your family on the kitchen table kind of thing."},{"time":237000,"text":"I can toss these things around. They're so much more tangible and touchable --"},{"time":240000,"text":"and you know I can double-click on something to take a look at it."},{"time":243000,"text":"And I can do all that kind of same stuff I showed you before."},{"time":245000,"text":"So I can pile things up, I can flip through it, I can, you know --"},{"time":248000,"text":"okay, let's move this photo to the back, let's delete this guy here,"},{"time":254000,"text":"and I think it's just a much more rich kind of way of interacting with your information."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258000,"text":"And that's BumpTop. Thanks!"}]}]}